oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Home Food Supply Program. Mr. & Mrs. M.C. Crandle, Lawrenceburg, Tennessee, R.F.D. #3.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Mr. & Mrs. Crandle failed to make ends meet in the northwest where wheat alone was grown; they came to Lawrence County in the fall of 1930 and paid $2,625 for 75 acres of land.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Agriculture; Farms; Spouses
